<subSubSection pageId="21" pageNumber="44" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="21.[151,760,1800,2047]" lastBlockId="21.[828,1437,190,405]" pageId="21" pageNumber="44">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,281,1800,1823]" pageId="21" pageNumber="44">Comments.</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="JACOBY M." box="[289,457,1800,1823]" pageId="21" pageNumber="44" pagination="377 - 501" refId="ref31521" refString="JACOBY M. 1896 a: Descriptions of the new genera and species of phytophagous Coleoptera obtained by Dr. Modigliani in Sumatra. Annali del Museo Civico di Storia Naturale di Genova 36: 377 - 501." type="journal article" year="1896">JACOBY (1896a)</bibRefCitation>
described this species from two specimens and classified it in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Baly" authorityYear="1864" box="[521,650,1832,1855]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Platyxantha" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="44" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[521,650,1832,1855]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="44">Platyxantha</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. This was followed by 
<bibRefCitation author="WEISE J." box="[279,420,1864,1887]" pageId="21" pageNumber="44" pagination="1 - 225" refId="ref33576" refString="WEISE J. 1924: Pars 78: Chrysomelidae: 13. Galerucinae. In: SCHENK- LING S. (ed.): Coleopterorum Catalogus. W. Junk, Berlin, pp. 1 - 225." type="book chapter" year="1924">WEISE (1924)</bibRefCitation>
. For an unknown reason, 
<bibRefCitation author="WILCOX J. A." pageId="21" pageNumber="44" pagination="433 - 664" refId="ref33616" refString="WILCOX J. A. 1973: Chrysomelidae: Galerucinae: Luperini: Luperina. In: WILCOX J. A. (ed.): Coleopterorum Catalogus Supplementa. Pars 78 (3). Editio seconda. W. Junk, ' s-Gravenhage, pp. 433 - 664." type="book chapter" year="1973">WILCOX (1973)</bibRefCitation>
classified it in 
<taxonomicName authorityName=", MOHAMEDSAID" authorityYear="1998" box="[384,485,1896,1919]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Polexima" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="44" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[384,485,1896,1919]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="44">Polexima</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
which probably caused it to be omitted by 
<bibRefCitation author="REID C. A. M." box="[338,470,1928,1951]" pageId="21" pageNumber="44" pagination="1 - 9" refId="ref33192" refString="REID C. A. M. 1999: Reappraisal of the genus Taumacera Thunberg with descriptions of two new species from South-East Asia (Coleoptera: Chrysomelidae: Galerucinae). Australian Journal of Entomology 38: 1 - 9." type="journal article" year="1999">REID (1999)</bibRefCitation>
. I examined both 
<typeStatus box="[666,759,1928,1951]" pageId="21" pageNumber="44">syntypes</typeStatus>
(females) deposited in the BMNH and MSNG. Because the assignment in 
<taxonomicName authorityName=", MOHAMEDSAID" authorityYear="1998" box="[345,446,1992,2015]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Polexima" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="44" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[345,446,1992,2015]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="44">Polexima</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is evidently wrong as it is an African genus, I tentatively transfer 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Jacoby" authorityYear="1896" box="[560,728,2024,2047]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Platyxantha" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="44" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="submetallica">
<emphasis box="[560,728,2024,2047]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="44">P. submetallica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Thunberg" authorityYear="1814" box="[828,947,190,213]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Taumacera" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="44" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[828,947,190,213]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="44">Taumacera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. However, the correct generic placement can only be resolved when a male is discovered.As mentioned already by 
<bibRefCitation author="JACOBY M." box="[948,1115,254,277]" pageId="21" pageNumber="44" pagination="377 - 501" refId="ref31521" refString="JACOBY M. 1896 a: Descriptions of the new genera and species of phytophagous Coleoptera obtained by Dr. Modigliani in Sumatra. Annali del Museo Civico di Storia Naturale di Genova 36: 377 - 501." type="journal article" year="1896">JACOBY (1896a)</bibRefCitation>
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Jacoby" baseAuthorityYear="1896" box="[1122,1390,254,277]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Platyxantha" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="44" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="multicostata">
<emphasis box="[1122,1390,254,277]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="44">Platyxantha multicostata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Jacoby" authorityYear="1896" box="[828,992,286,309]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Platyxantha" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="44" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="submetallica">
<emphasis box="[828,992,286,309]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="44">P. submetallica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
could belong to a single species as they were collected at the same locality (Si-Rambé) and differ only in the body length and paler colouration of the elytral disc in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Jacoby" authorityYear="1896" box="[905,1067,382,405]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Platyxantha" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="44" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="submetallica">
<emphasis box="[905,1067,382,405]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="44">P. submetallica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
